      "span_text": "In fact, it is easy to see that if M has no 1's (and so it corresponds to a graph H as explained above), then a perfect graph G has an M -partition if and only if G does not contain a clique of size greater than the maximum clique of H. However, it was shown in  that if each M -partition problem for perfect graphs is polynomial or NP-complete, then the Dichotomy Conjecture mentioned earlier holds."
